      <p class="moreinfo">The law of conservation of momentum states that the momentum of two objects before collision is equal to the momentum of both objects after the collision.</p>
      <p class="moreinfo">The momentum of a single object is its mass times its velocity (p = m * v). Its kinetic energy is half the mass times the square of the velocity (K = <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> m * v<sup>2</sup>).</p>
